^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Patti's overcall is a tad light, but certainly has some merit. Had she had a singleton spade and 3 small diamonds, it would have been clear cut. Now, as to Dee. She certainly has a very nice hand. However, it does have some flaws. First of all, it is rare that you can make slam after an opening bid, unless you are very distributional. Second, the KJ of spades are not pulling their full weight. So, I think a simple 4H bid is probably best. That happens to go down as well, but that is because everything is offside (not a huge surprise) and Patti is a bit light. |
PG| ***** 10 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One other point about Dee's decision making. Her 2S bid had merit, if she thought there might be slam. However, once Patti bids 3H, which is the weakest bid there is, she should just bid 4H. Her thinking was not consistent. 2S is a limit raise. You are not even in a game force. So, 3H says Patti is not willing to play 4H opposite a limit raise. The point I was trying to make was that once Dee bids 2S, and Patti makes a weak bid, she should be consistent and bid 4H.|
PG| ***** 11 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If she was planning to bid 4N over whatever Patti bid, then she might as well bid it to start with.|
