^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, lets talk about the auction here. Six diamonds goes down on a spade lead and Dee found the only defense that lets us make 6N. First, let me say that I strongly prefer DONT to CAPP, particularly over the strong NT. DONT lets you compete at the 2 level, whereas cap often forces you to the 3 level. Over weak NT, CAPP has more merit, because it does allow penalty doubles. But I don't think penalty doubles are useful in real life even over a weak NT. In the 40 years I have been playing weak NT, I have only successfully been penalized less than a dozen times. So, if you want to adopt a bid that is successful once every 3 years, be my guest. |
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now as to whether Dee should bid DONT. I think she has one of 2 choices. She should either pass or go for the gusto and bid 3H. Double sort of accomplishes very little. 3H is very aggressive, but it has some upside. Now let's look at Patti's hand. She actually has a rule of 20 opener, if you use Marty Bergen's upgrade for the quality club suit. However, I would not open Patti's hand at the one level, Marty Bergen would probably recommend she open it 2S, as he likes to lay claim to the spade suit, and doesn't mind opening weak 2s with a 5 card suit when appropriate. 3C is another possibility. But I think pass is ok as well. |
PG| ***** 26 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next. let's discuss what I play over strong NT, in terms of a slam try. If Dee had passed, I play all 3 level bids are slam tries. So, playing with one of my regular partners, I would bid 3D with Roberta's hand. If the NT bidder likes diamonds, then he begins control bidding. I suspect what would have happened is I would bid 3H over 3D and roberta would bid 4C. Then, I would bid 4N and go to six. If Dee finds a spade lead we are down. If not we make.  |
PG| ***** 27 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, if you play systems on over interference, then roberta could still bid 3D. But, given we have no understanding, 3N seems like the best bid. If they run hearts, so be it.|
PG| ***** 28 ***** |


