NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Opener sometimes has a problem as well. If opener has 18+, then opener must force to game. Therefore, opener must make a bid that forces another bid out of responder, assuming responder has not made a game force. So, for example, in this case, suppose Patti had decided to bid 3C. Roberta has the option of passing. But not on this hand, as she has a game force. So, over 3C, she would have to bid 3D, asking Patti to bid 3N with a diamond stopper. On reverse auctions, it is not clear who is captain of the bidding, which is why it is complicated.|
