HT|g|CP||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|As much as anything else, balancing is a state of mind. When the opponents stop bidding at a low level, you should not simply breathe a sigh of relief that they didn't bid game. 

Instead, your attitude should be: 
"They're trying to buy the contract at a low level. No way!! Who do they think they are playing against -- children?  If they think they can buy the contract at a low level against me, they are sadly mistaken." Instead of meekly rolling over, you should roll up your sleeves and find something to say. After all, if they lack the strength for game, your partner must have something. This hand is an example of what will be discussed at the lesson:|
